data.enText: to walk in a slow relaxed way

data.chText: 他悠闲地走过，仿佛时间对他来说是无穷无尽的。
data.enText: He sauntered by, looking as if he had all the time in the world.
This part of the route should be an easy saunter.

tr: a leisurely walk (usually in some public place)

example: he walked with a kind of saunter as if he hadn't a care in the world

tr: walk leisurely and with no apparent aim

value.def: If you saunter somewhere, you walk there in a slow, casual way.

example.ex: We watched our fellow students saunter into the building...
example.tran: 我们看着同学们悠闲地走进了大楼。

example.ex: He sauntered along the river to the mill.
example.tran: 他沿着河边漫步走到磨坊。

example.ex: She began a slow saunter toward the bonfires.
example.tran: 她开始向篝火处慢慢走去。
